Date added: 2016-01-22 || Action: Client Visit || Met him and Thin Ei Phyo (HR manager) as a client at MAB HQ.  MAB is owned by U Chit Khaing, Edin Group, the same group that owns, large scale construction in Nay Pyi Daw, F&B - Fuji Cafe & Restaurant, Signature - management partnership with Hilton group, hotels in Nay Pyi Daw and Ngapali, and Hotel Thingaha,  Denko - upstream oil importer.  


Have 73 MAB branches throughout Myanmar so far - 14 in Yangon and 8 in Mandalay. Will open 20-25 branches within 2016. Has in house team - use 6 search and recruitment firms. My jobs (2 months guarantee) and executive search (1-3 months guarantee, not very clear line depends on the position) for repat and local entry to mid level positions, 2 Singapore search firms (2 months guarantee) and 1 Brunei Search (3 months guarantee- 50% refund if they can't find the candidate + other services) firms for senior positions. Right now, only 5 expats in Management team - CFO, HOI, IR and 2 more. 
For entry and mid positions, MAB spends 15%
For senior positions, 18-25% (negotiated the terms with the firms though their terms were 20-25%).

He does recruitment for senior position for the whole Eden group. Got in contact with Singapore search firm when he was working for IGE. 

They are concerned our terms are higher than the firm they are using now. Will submit it to management and negotiate the term if they are interested.
